Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,当我还是个实习生 或者第一年受训的医生\NWhen I was an intern, or a first-year doctor in training, 
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.96,0:00:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,我就知道我的状态出了问题\NI knew something was wrong with me. 
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.88,0:00:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,我时常失眠 郁郁寡欢\N I had trouble sleeping, I had difficulty feeling joy,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.04,0:00:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,我会在不合适的时候有哭泣的冲动\NI was prone to crying at inopportune times.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.90,0:00:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,更糟糕的是 我难以和病人沟通\NEven worse, I had trouble connecting with patients. 
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.56,0:00:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,我觉得我不能让任何人感到高兴\NI felt like I couldn't please anyone, 
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.64,0:00:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,我发现我and I found myself susceptible to feelings of despair and panic.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.18,0:00:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a physician! And if I do say so myself, a very well trained one.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.02,0:00:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet it took an intern support group, the social worker that ran it,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.52,0:00:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,close friends and my then fiancee and now wife 
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.84,0:00:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,to convince me that I might need help. 
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.84,0:00:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if I couldn't acknowledge it, 
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.84,0:00:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,they could see I was suffering from depression. 
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.00,0:00:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't alone! that's the topic of this week's healthcare triage.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.46,0:00:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Last month the study in JAMA 
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.00,0:00:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,reviewed all the literature on depression and depressive symptoms in resident physicians.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.36,0:00:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,They found more than 50 studies on the subject. 
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.38,0:00:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Researches show that almost 30% of resident physician
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.94,0:01:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,suffer from either symptoms, or a diagnosis of depression. 
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.28,0:01:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The numbers and how they compare to other professions are almost beside the point.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.52,0:01:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Physicians are in a unique position of needing to care for others continuously,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.60,0:01:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,that strain coupled with an inability to help themselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.20,0:01:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,leaves both patients and doctors at risk.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.08,0:01:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Longitudinal studies or those that follow resident over the course of their training, 
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.20,0:01:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,found that the rate of depressive issues in residents 
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.08,0:01:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,increased more than 15 percent within a year of beginning training. 
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.96,0:01:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Worse, physicians exist in a profession where admitting a problem 
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.36,0:01:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,carries with it a stigma that's more impactful than in some others.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.96,0:01:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,A study published in 2008 surveyed physicians in Michigan, 
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.72,0:01:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,asking them about their work experiences as well as their depressive symptoms. 
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.06,0:01:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,More than 11 percent reported moderate to severe depression scores. 
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.64,0:01:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,About a quarter of them reported knowing a doctor 
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.50,0:01:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,whose professional standing had been hurt by being depressed. 
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.40,0:01:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Physicians with moderate to severe depression 
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.50,0:01:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,had a decrease in work productivity and job satisfaction. 
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.68,0:01:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,They were also two to three times more likely to say 
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.78,0:02:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that they were worried about or had difficulty getting mental health care 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.44,0:02:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,while the Americans with Disabilities Act passed in 1990 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.76,0:02:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,prohibits employers from asking broad questions about illnesses when people apply for jobs,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.56,0:02:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,state medical licensing board still ask specific questions about mental health.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.22,0:02:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of this, physicians are much more likely to avoid treatment 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.84,0:02:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,but also more likely to self medicate. 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.06,0:02:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes that medication is potentially appropriate, as with anti-depressants. 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.20,0:02:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Often it is not. 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.20,0:02:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,A 2012 study in JAMA surgery found that 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.40,0:02:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,more than 15% of the members of the American College of Surgeons 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.26,0:02:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,had a score on screening test consistent with alcohol abuse or dependence. 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.24,0:02:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Among female surgeons the prevalence was more than 25%. 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.44,0:02:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who were depressed were significantly more likely to abuse or be dependent on alcohol.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.52,0:02:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,doctors have much easier access to drugs than others as well. 
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.02,0:02:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of this they are more likely to misuse prescription drugs than the general population.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.42,0:03:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Anesthesiologist have access to even more drugs than other physicians 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.66,0:03:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and their problems are even more common. 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.80,0:03:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,A 2005 study of anesthesia residency training programs,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.40,0:03:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,found that eighty percent of them reported experiences with impaired residents
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.70,0:03:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and almost 20% had experiences with at least one abuse-related death of a doctrine training.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.90,0:03:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, depression and substance abuse can lead to further problems including suicide 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.66,0:03:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,more than 6 percent of surgeons report suicidal ideation in the last year 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.34,0:03:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,yet only one-quarter of then sought any kind of mental health treatment. 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.10,0:03:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Most who did not fear the doing so would affect their ability to obtain a license, 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.38,0:03:37.90,Default,,0,0,0,,even though they were worried about killing themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.90,0:03:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem is even worse among medical trainees. 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.12,0:03:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,About 6 percent of them reported thinking about suicide in the last two weeks. 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.10,0:03:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Those with a history of depression 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.10,0:03:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,were almost four times as likely to report recent suicidal thoughts as those without. 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.84,0:03:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Too many doctors act on suicidal impulses as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.98,0:03:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It's estimated that about 400 physicians commit suicide each year, 
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.20,0:04:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,that's about three times as many doctors 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.58,0:04:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,as were in my medical school class at the University of Pennsylvania. 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.66,0:04:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Meta-analyses estimate the rate of suicide among male physicians 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.82,0:04:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,is a hundred and forty percent that of the general population.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.94,0:04:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Among female physicians it's almost two hundred and thirty percent. 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.90,0:04:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What makes this important to discuss 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.46,0:04:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,is not theprevalence of depression in physicians and trainees, 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.50,0:04:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,although it's clearly too high, 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.96,0:04:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,\Nit's not whether physicians have the highest suicide rate of any professional, 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.68,0:04:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,although many people argue that they do. 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.60,0:04:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The critical issue here is that too many physicians especially trainees 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.58,0:04:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,suffer in silence, afraid to ask for help 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.50,0:04:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,for fear that they will be punished professionally if not personally. 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.76,0:04:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I've always been very open about my time in residency,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.50,0:04:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and how depression someone robbed me of a few years of my life. 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.64,0:04:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,When I look back, I think the constant pressure to help others 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.86,0:04:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,coupled with frequent feelings of helplessness wait on me, 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.60,0:04:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,a lack of sleep and being away from family and friends left me vulnerable. 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.92,0:04:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Seeing children I've bonded with and cared for deeply suffer and die 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.14,0:05:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,was often more than I could bear. 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.14,0:05:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think some part of me whether it be physical or behavioral 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.76,0:05:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,is also predisposed to anxiety and depression. 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.36,0:05:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm lucky, thanks to the support of those who love me 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.22,0:05:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as two excellent therapist, I'm no longer depressed. 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.58,0:05:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I remain vigilant, however, against a recurrence. 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.42,0:05:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's important for me and for all physicians to stay on top of their mental health 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.22,0:05:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and not wait for a crisis to act. 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.10,0:05:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I've also felt fortunate to be in a specialty: pediatrics and a focus: research
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.02,0:05:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,where I didn't fear being found out. 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.22,0:05:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Many colleagues still recoil when I talked openly about therapy, 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.82,0:05:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,or how I plan to go for the rest of my life. 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.98,0:05:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure they'll find this episode concerning as well. 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.06,0:05:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But we can't not talk about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.86,0:05:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Too many of us are suffering and if they can't get help from others, 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.36,0:05:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,they may try and fail to help themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.20,0:05:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Suicide is always a tragedy. A physician committing suicide is a travesty.
